covered: Valid Request scenarios: Numerous TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC18 cover successful retrievals with various parameter combinations.
Empty response handling: TC04 and TC05 validate empty results when no matches or empty DB.
Query Parameters: Wide coverage of valid/invalid combos (offset, limit, accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA, audit) across TC02, TC03, TC04–TC08, TC12–TC13, TC14.
Pagination: Multiple scenarios exercise offset/limit and multi-page expectations (TC02, TC03, TC15).
Authorization: Tests for missing and invalid tokens (TC09, TC10).
Error handling: Invalid input scenarios (TC06, TC07, TC08) and service errors (TC11, TC19).
Security: SQL injection and XSS scenarios (TC12, TC13).
Regression/backward compatibility: Empty searchKey and older client behavior (TC17, TC18).
gaps: Caching Behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache effectiveness.
Rate Limiting: While TC15 covers concurrency, explicit rate-limiting/throttling behavior and guarantees are not validated.
Authorization breadth: Only 401 cases tested; no 403 for insufficient privileges scenario.
Edge-case pagination: No tests explicitly asserting behavior when requesting pages beyond available data or exact boundary conditions beyond basic offsets.
Performance metrics: TL;DR similar to TC15, but no concrete SLA or measured response times beyond one scenario.
Malformed/extra parameters: Some tests cover extra parameters (TC14), but broader validation of unexpected types or combinations could be enhanced.
recommendations: Add tests for caching behavior, including presence and correctness of caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation scenarios.
Include explicit rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., burst of requests within short interval) and verify retry/429 handling if supported.
Extend authorization tests to cover 403 Forbidden scenarios (insufficient permissions) in addition to 401 unauthorized.
Add explicit pagination boundary tests (e.g., last page, beyond last item, exact page counts) and verify correct item counts, ordering, and total from metadata if available.
Incorporate performance-focused tests with defined SLA expectations (e.g., max latency per page under load) and more varied concurrent loads.
Expand input validation tests for edge-case and malformed parameter types (e.g., extremely large numbers, mixed-type parameters) and confirm proper error messaging.
